  "body": "From the spec:\r\n\r\nCompute `parent_hashes = [get_block_hash(active_state, block, slot - CYCLE_LENGTH + i) for i in range(1, CYCLE_LENGTH - len(oblique_parent_hashes) + 1)] + oblique_parent_hashes`. \r\neg, if `CYCLE_LENGTH = 4`, `slot = 5`, the actual block hashes starting from slot 0 are `Z A B C D E F G H I J`, and `oblique_parent_hashes = [D', E']` then `parent_hashes = [B, C, D' E'])`\r\n\r\nThis is fairly different from our [current implementation](https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/master/beacon-chain/types/active_state.go#L201). This ticket should align our implementation with the spec. The new slice should be initialized with a capacity of `CYCLE_LENGTH` to avoid unnecessary memory allocation and copy.",
